From 5014ca0ecdd138afeaf54e12840c73739c06bb7f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 12:38:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add appointments, HIPAA training, messaging, BMI charts &
 admin portal
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Member features:
- Scheduling & appointments: bookable services (personal training, nutrition,
  pelvic health, boxing, kids athletics, holistic coaching), request/confirm
  flow, virtual meeting links and iCalendar (.ics) export
- HIPAA privacy training with a knowledge-check quiz, sign-off and certificate
- Secure messaging with the care team (member <-> admin only)
- BMI trend chart + category gauge integrated into the dashboard

Admin portal (custom-built; see note on administrate below):
- Overview with KPIs, "needs attention" flags and trend charts
- Members directory + full read-only member chart
- "Help diagnose": rule-based HealthInsights flags + clinical assessments
- Appointment management (confirm/cancel/complete, meeting links)
- Conversations (DM) inbox with unread tracking
- Service catalog management
- Analytics: bookings by service, weekly check-ins/signups, workout mix,
  training completion and wellbeing distribution
- Admin-only access guard + admin layout/navigation

Foundations: User role enum (member/admin), 8 migrations, 6 new models.
Quality: 41 tests / 123 assertions, RuboCop clean, Brakeman 0 warnings.

Note: evaluated the `administrate` gem (v0.20.1) as requested and did NOT
adopt it — it requires Rails < 8.0 (this app is Rails 8.1) and pulls in
sassc-rails/jquery-rails/selectize-rails which conflict with our propshaft +
import map pipeline. Built a brand-consistent custom admin instead.

